                    <strong>Example Answer:</strong> <em>"The Menu Actions Pattern reduces cognitive overload by presenting users with organized, clear options instead of overwhelming them with all possible information at once. This is important because it allows users to focus on exactly what they need, leading to faster task completion and higher satisfaction rates."</em>
